  34:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   *** RTC Wakeup configuration ***
  35:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   ================================
  36:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   [..]
  37:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) To configure the RTC Wakeup Clock source and Counter use the
  38:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         HAL_RTCEx_SetWakeUpTimer() function.
  39:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         You can also configure the RTC Wakeup timer in interrupt mode using the
  40:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         HAL_RTCEx_SetWakeUpTimer_IT() function.
  41:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) To read the RTC Wakeup Counter register, use the HAL_RTCEx_GetWakeUpTimer()
  42:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         function.
  43:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c **** 
  44:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   *** Timestamp configuration ***
  45:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   ===============================
  46:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   [..]
  47:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) To configure the RTC Timestamp use the HAL_RTCEx_SetTimeStamp() function.
  48:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         You can also configure the RTC Timestamp with interrupt mode using the
  49:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         HAL_RTCEx_SetTimeStamp_IT() function.
  50:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) To read the RTC Timestamp Time and Date register, use the
  51:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         HAL_RTCEx_GetTimeStamp() function.
  52:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) The Timestamp alternate function is mapped to RTC_AF1 (PC13).
  53:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c **** 
  54:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   *** Tamper configuration ***
  55:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   ============================
  56:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   [..]
  57:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) To enable the RTC Tamper and configure the Tamper filter count, trigger
  58:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         Edge or Level according to the Tamper filter value (if equal to 0 Edge
  59:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         else Level), sampling frequency, NoErase, MaskFlag, precharge or
  60:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         discharge and Pull-UP use the HAL_RTCEx_SetTamper() function.
  61:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         You can configure RTC Tamper in interrupt mode using HAL_RTCEx_SetTamper_IT()
  62:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         function.
  63:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) The default configuration of the Tamper erases the backup registers.
  64:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         To avoid this, enable the NoErase field on the RTC_TAMPCR register.
  65:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) The TAMPER1 alternate function is mapped to RTC_AF1 (PC13).
  66:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) The TAMPER2 alternate function is mapped to RTC_AF2 (PA0).
  67:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) The TAMPER3 alternate function is mapped to RTC_AF3 (PE6).
  68:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c **** 
  69:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   *** Backup Data Registers configuration ***
  70:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   ===========================================
  71:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   [..]
  72:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) To write to the RTC Backup Data registers, use the HAL_RTCEx_BKUPWrite()
  73:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         function.
  74:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) To read the RTC Backup Data registers, use the HAL_RTCEx_BKUPRead()
  75:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         function.
  76:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c **** 
  77:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   *** Smooth Digital Calibration configuration ***
  78:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   ================================================
  79:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   [..]
  80:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) RTC frequency can be digitally calibrated with a resolution of about
  81:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         0.954 ppm with a range from -487.1 ppm to +488.5 ppm.
  82:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         The correction of the frequency is performed using a series of small
  83:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         adjustments (adding and/or subtracting individual RTCCLK pulses).
  84:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) The smooth digital calibration is performed during a cycle of about 2^20
  85:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         RTCCLK pulses (or 32 seconds) when the input frequency is 32,768 Hz.
  86:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         This cycle is maintained by a 20-bit counter clocked by RTCCLK.
  87:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) The smooth calibration register (RTC_CALR) specifies the number of RTCCLK
  88:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         clock cycles to be masked during the 32-second cycle.
ARM GAS  C:\Users\Tilen\AppData\Local\Temp\ccvNaC6x.s 			page 3


  89:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) To configure the RTC Smooth Digital Calibration value and the corresponding
  90:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         calibration cycle period (32s,16s and 8s) use the HAL_RTCEx_SetSmoothCalib()
  91:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         function.
  92:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c **** 
  93:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   *** Outputs configuration ***
  94:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   =============================
  95:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   [..] The RTC has 2 different outputs:
  96:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) RTC_ALARM: this output is used to manage the RTC alarms (Alarm A and Alarm B)
  97:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         and WaKeUp signals.
  98:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         To output the selected RTC signal, use the HAL_RTC_Init() function.
  99:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) RTC_CALIB: this output is 512Hz signal or 1Hz.
 100:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         To enable the RTC_CALIB, use the HAL_RTCEx_SetCalibrationOutPut() function.
 101:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) Two pins can be used as RTC_ALARM or RTC_CALIB output, selected through
 102:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         bit OUT_RMP of the RTC_OR register:
 103:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         - (PC13, PB14) for STM32L05x/6x/7x/8x
 104:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         - (PA2, PB14) for STM32L03x/4x
 105:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) When the RTC_CALIB or RTC_ALARM output is selected, the RTC_OUT pin is
 106:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         automatically configured in output alternate function.
 107:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c **** 
 108:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   @endverbatim
 109:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   ******************************************************************************
